,Recommended,255710,15347139,"Posted: 13 April, 2015",all,DeekFTW,"This game is phenomenal. Not since I first bought and downloaded Minecraft have I played one game for such a long period of time without switching to another game here or there. This game has the feel of a early RollerCoaster Tycoon game where you can tell the developers took pride in creating and perfecting every little detail and aspect of the game. This game is extremely addicting in the best way possible. Your city, the city that you watch rise out of a field of grass, feels alive. There is always a buzz around town and you truly feel like you and your civs are in it together. You feel a sense of obligation to your fellow city members after a while. If there is a traffic problem, you want to fix it for their sake and your own. After you fix that first problem, you look to improve another aspect of how your city is planned. After that, there is something else to improve. You can see why it is so hard to bank that final save of the night and hit that quit button.There are a few little things here and there that aren't perfect in the game yet. Some UI tweaks are needed and the driving AI is in need of an overhaul but for a game that was developed by a team of under 20 people a few minor issues are to be expected. I've seen blockbuster titles being released with more issues than this game. Mod support is incredible in this game as well. I've never seen such a seamless integration with the steam workshop in a game. If there is an issue that you have with an aspect of this game, there is very likely a mod that will change it for you.I would say I have definitely gotten my money's worth out of this game already and I don't intend on putting it down in the near future. I can only say thank you to a development team that deserves the high praise that this game has garnered. I can only hope that they keep making games that are as simple yet deep with gameplay as Cities: Skylines in the future."
