76561198025114911,Recommended,255710,14896980,"Posted: 14 March, 2015",all,Duke CakeFace,Best sim builder I have ever played.
,Recommended,255710,14957281,"Posted: 19 March, 2015",all,Time4DinDins,"I wouldnt want to start this review like this, but it can't be helped so let's get it over with:There is this genre of videogames called City Builders, the first of which, which is also the most influential for at least the first 4 iterations, is Simcity. It was such a genre defining game that it's hard to separate the term ""City Builder"" from the game ""Simcity"". But in taking a look at Cities: Skylines, we need to define that ofently blurred line.CS (or Cities Skylines as I will refer to for the rest of the review) is a game that falls behind the City Builder genre. It bears a huge resemblance to the Simcity games mostly, because it concerns the act of building and managing cities.Lets start of with the vague similarities:You build roads, you zone areas, you build civic service buildings, manage traffic, get awarded unique buildings for certain achievements, manage budget and make sure everyone has access to electricity and water, et-cetera.Given this, it's hard to separate CS from Simcity, and if at this point you still havent managed to do that, then you're probably better off playing a modded version of Simcity 4 for all of eternity.What exactly separates CS from Simcity?Firstly : the quirky, humorous and iconic ""character"" of the Simcity games is not present. You wont find wittily written lines that can be found on building names, sim complaints or even the loading screen. CS is a light-hearted city builder that offers a touch of personality to save the game from being overly generic and bland, that's all.Second, which is the best part: Where CS lacks personality, it makes up for with all of Simcity's features AND THEN SOME. Take all of the tools, and pump it with steroids until it's about to burst. The game offers you all the necessary tools for you to take on any problem easily, seamlessly and intuitively.With all that's said and done, CS is a game that holds it's own and builds it's own brand in the City Building genre. Robust tools, great graphics, good music (occasionaly tries to be too epic), this is a definitey buy for all city building fans, or those who are curious and want to dip their toes into this wonderful genre."
