76561198036745772,Recommended,255710,29450172,Posted: 23 January,all,dd31879,"Cities Skylines still remains one of the best city builders available in terms of flexibility, available space, mods, and so on.In terms of available space you get a gigantic 9 tile area to work in by default. Which can be expanded with the 25 tile unlock mod. Since maps are different and inevitably cities get built different every time you play you don't unlock these tiles in any particular order either. You just purchase any tile that is next to another tile you already own. Which means you are not locked down to a simple square.There is a LOT of community content now. The game has been out for a while and the workshop is full of mods, maps, and assets to make your game better.  Of course I always recommend first play throughs be straight up vanilla just to get a feel for the unmodded a game. However, there are some real benefits to using mods.That said though I really can not recommend any of the paid DLCs other than After Dark. This was the first DLC they released and it still seems like the most impactful to date. I would have to say that what makes it better is that it provides things that are useful in building the city or in managing the city. This would be, as example, like the Bus Terminal which is an almost necessary thing for managing your city. Using it you can easily see how many of your citizens will travel between your various routes.Snowfall and Natural Disasters on the other hand always seemed, to me at least, more gimmicky than really helpful. Like they were just put in to say ""here is new content. enjoy!"" but they really didnt help anything like After Dark did.The Snowfall DLC pretty much only gives you the street car (tram) service to help with actually managing your city and everything else is just winter flavored Skylines. Actually one might even say that Snowfall is more hassle that its worth since you have to build in an all white zone which people have complained many times about this causing eye strain and headaches. Then you have specialized services for heating and road maintenance which eats up more of your city resources than you normally would.Natural Disasters is kinda one of those things i remember from the first SimCity game I played as a kid. I remember working on my city and having the a tornado or godzilla go through the city and destroy things. Then I would have to rebuild. Seemed like might be interesting. Not so much though to be honest.Where in that old game when you didnt have much else to worry about except placing power lines and roads... this game you have a lot more to worry about. Probably the least threatening aspect here is the forest fires, but everything else if it hits your city can really be a problem. The thing I find the worst about this, and I have seen this thought elsewhere too, is that I have to spend so many hours building up a great city then a disaster comes and smashes things. Which I am not even one that goes overboard with a huge amount of detail! I have seen streamers that really micromanage on the details and if I put that level of detail in only to have it destroyed I would quit playing.Mass Transit Will be coming out soon and it promises to be another good DLC that will be helpful in many ways. What is known about it right now is that there will be new public transportation added in the paid DLC which will help in managing the city better and the free patch that goes along with the DLC release will have a LOT of quality of life changes which are focused on traffic and transportation.Here is a run down of the DLC content:After Dark:Added PrisonsAdded District Specializations (Industry and Commercial)Added Taxi ServiceAdded Bus Terminal (handles multiple bus lines where citizens can go to change between lines)Added Bicycles and Bicycle Pathssee the full patch here:http://www.skylineswiki.com/Patch_1.2.0Snow Fall:Added Winter ThemeAdded Tram ServiceAdded Snow Plow (only on snow maps obviously)Added more energy consumption and heating requirements (..on the snow maps)see the full patch here:http://www.skylineswiki.com/Patch_1.3.0-f4Natural Disasters:Added 7 DisastersAdded Early Warning System (to warn you about disasters happening)Added Helicopter (fire, medical, and police)Added Evacuation Routes (for disaster events)see the full patch here:http://www.skylineswiki.com/Patch_1.6.0Mass Transit:Added MonorailsAdded BlimpsAdded Cable CarsAdded FerriesAdded Transport Hubs (multi-transit buildings ex. monorail+bus terminal)see the full patch here: TBA"
