76561198095692807,Recommended,255710,31809885,Posted: 17 May,all,Wstar555,"I love this game, it has detail and is nearly the same as behing a actual mayor, without the paperwork of course :p You get to face the some problems as a actual mayor: traffic, money, pollution, industry and many more. Most players and me have all problems with this, traffic. Traffic is easy in the beginning of the game, but gets progressively more difficult as your city grows, lucky we have public transportation; Busses, Trains and subways. Planes and boats  provide tourists/cargo, trains also bring trourists and cargo.Money is generated by offices, industry, shops, taxes and more. In the beginning, money is a bit of a problem but later it will become easier to manage money.Pollution and industry go hand in hand, Industry creates pollution, causing ilnesses to citizens.The game doesnt give you all the features right from the start, you have to meet certain goals to level up and get acces to different services so the game doesnt get too complicated right from the start. You get better things as your town evolves from hamlet to Metropolis and all the ranks between it. The criteria to level up is based on citizen numbers, if you want to level up you need a certain ammount of citizen in your town like take for example 380 citizens to level up to a hamlet witch meens 380 citzens have to live in your town to be a hamlet, if that population goes under 380 that doesnt mean your rank goes down.There is a lot of Dlc's like Natural disasters, which adds disasters to the game that make the game more challenging.I love the newest dlc named: mass transit, it adds more public transit to the game like Blimps for air transport, ferries for water transport in canals, monorails that can travel above roads, saving space. There are cable cars for simple transport over mountains.On the cons:The dlc's are a bit pricy, but you do get really good quality for the money you spend.You will need a good computer to play it, visit the forums.That is my review of the game,Thx for reading!"
