76561197973206419,Recommended,255710,15208148,"Posted: 4 April, 2015",all,Madswitch,"If you want a fun-filled city builder that doesn't get lost in micromanagement, then this game is for you.  I always loved the earlier SimCity titles but I hated worrying about whether I could get the power or water to work.  After playing more casual builders like the Tropico series, I began to prefer that style over the more technical aspects of other management sims.  Cities: Skylines blends both of these worlds beautifully with all the benefits.Learning curve is fairly light so don't worry about whether you have the time to learn what the game has to offer.  I watched a 30 minute tutorial on YouTube and began playing immediately.  Sure the premise is simple but don't let that convince you that the game lacks complexity.  Managing traffic jams, proper zoning, passing policies all allow for a custom experience with tons of replay value.  At a modest $29.99 USD pricetag, you can't afford to wait!"
