,Recommended,255710,15124470,"Posted: 30 March, 2015",all,Kai,"Cities: Skylines is a city builder developed by Colossal Order, the folks who were responsible for making the Cities in Motion series, and published by Paradox Interactive, and I have to say this is hands down the best city builder we’ve ever had on Steam .The scale of the game is simply astonishing, by default the game features a 36km2 map which is almost 10 times the size of the map you’re given in SimCity 2013, and with the help of mods from the Steam Workshop, this can be expanded to 100 km2, which is absolutely enormous. Even though there are no interactions between cities in different maps, it is frankly not necessary, with the help of the powerful yet easy to use building tool, you can simply build multiple cities on a single map.Despite the humongous size, the developers paid close attention to details, in fact, detail is the word I’ll use to describe this game. From the entire traffic network, down to individual citizens, every aspect in Cities: Skylines are properly simulated. You’ll find trucks, colour coded depending on what they are currently carrying, delivering their cargos to their designated factories, citizen actually live in a permanent home, and ambulances that will rush to the scene, then little paramedics will get out of the vehicle, and few seconds later return with a patient on a stretcher.I also love how water works in this game as well as the fluid physics, it is completely unnecessary to have it in a city builder but at the same time it adds so much to experience, water have currents and flows, and you'll want to pump water on the upstream and set up sewage pipes on the opposite side, else you’ll start pumping polluted sewage water back into the system. You can even completely drain a lake dry, or accidently flooding your city because you just demolished a dam, playing with water have never been so fun.This is a city builder perfected, further enriched by the endless creativity of the community with the support of Steam Workshop, and lastly accompanied by an unprecedented scale. Cities: Skylines is a must buy for anyone who has the slightest interest in city buildiers, especially with the affordable launch price."
