76561198010195713,Recommended,255710,14936768,"Posted: 17 March, 2015",all,[189th]Darkwaver517,"Before I start the review, let me point out first that this game has a 96% recommendation ratio. So let that sink in for now.So, Cities: Skylines, or as I like to call it: How SimCity Should Have Been.It's really easy to draw comparisons to the EA IP, so let's do that real quick: This game does virtually everything that SimCity does, but better.It has somewhat the same mechanics but with a more user friendly touch to it. Skylines is overall just that, really user friendly. You'll find the learningcurve to be not steep at all. Once you get the hang of it in the first hour, you'll quickly start building your metropol.The difficulty of the game is set by your own creativity. Thats a shame because there is no real challange. If you want to build crazy shapes of roads or an unconventional city all together, youll find that there is de bottleneck. There are no disasters, and even if you mess up your finances or the entire structure of the city, the game will still be very forgiving.Besides that one downside on this game, there isn't anything to add to it. It's flawless in gameplay, there is a huge variety of third party content with the steam workshop implemented. And finally, the game is really addictive. There are plenty of things to unlock. From unique buildings to special types of roads. The game really has a nice pasing in that sence. Also, it looks amazing.So, without any real negative sides to this game, let me just say 'wow'. Buy it already!"
