,Recommended,255710,15453572,"Posted: 19 April, 2015",all,DeMexi,"It's what you hoped the sequel to Sim City 4 would be. All of the city building fun you'd expect, minus the tedious micro-management and clunky interface EA made us grow accustomed to.If there's one issue I have with the game, it would be its difficulty. The game starts of challenging, but once your city starts to take shape and you've managed to find some sort of balance, money will start rolling in and the hard part'll be over. The game is also a bit light on content, meaning you'll run out of new types of buildings to construct somewhere down the line.Personally, it doesn't bother me that much. Watching your citizens go about their business and your buildings evolve is more than enough fun in itself. Managing the various aspects involved with city planning is a rewarding task and, due to the game's intuitive interface, a fun one as well.And luckily, there is a large scala of mods that improve the game by adding to the gameplay or content. You'll definitely want to shift through the most popular mods before you get started with the game.All in all, I'd say: play it."
