76561198168853433,Recommended,255710,21040118,"Posted: 7 February, 2016",all,jsCP94,"An awesome city building simulatorI can't get enough of this game. I think it's enough of an endorsement to say that I played 100 hrs. vanilla-style, with no mods whatsoever, and I enjoyed every minute of it. However, it became much more enjoyable once I decided to use mods.What's there to say? You build roads, set aside land for houses, shops and factories; you build parks, hosipitals, police stations, etc. to service your city.  The customization is incredible, not even including mods. The ""simulation"" part with the Cims is also awesome and breathes life and spirit into the city. Yes, there is limitations, as eventually you see many of the exact same buildings repeated again and again. However, there is enough diversity of the buildings for me to be immersed in the city I built (again, this was before mods).If there's one thing that annoyed me though, it's building the roads. If I tried to make them the same length (and often one road wasslightlylonger than the other, then the perpendicular road connecting the parallel road would be slightly off. Yes, I could turn snapping off, but that messed up the city planning and the zoning, and I couldn't optimize area usage. Often, I had to build one parallel roads somewhat longer than the other in order to connect them with a perpendicular road. This results in me wasting money (or time if I made a big mistake and wanted to reload a previous save file). I wish there were more zones that were available when it comes to curved roads. Also, I wanted the traffic in the ""vanilla game"" to be more realistic (yes, I know there's a mod for that, I'm currently using it).But all in all, that's a nitpick in an otherwise great game."
