76561197998701258,Recommended,255710,14986131,"Posted: 21 March, 2015",all,Psygnal,"This is an excellent city building game, which puts the latest Sim City pretty much to shame.It is beautifully crafted, relatively well balanced (tweaks are still in progress) and just so damn detailed.It's pretty special straight off the shelf, but if you feel like modding, I can recommend you get one of the First Person ones that lets you get right down to street level, because actually walking around the city you've just built is very cool - and you get to see all the little details that you just don't see from 100 feet up.If you know about the Sim City style games, you'll know what to expect.  It's not too fiddly about it though.If you don't know about that stype of game ... essentially:Place roads, pop your residential/commercial/industrial zones down, make sure there's enough power and water, and watch your city start to grow.   You'll need to manage traffic, population density, crime, emergency services, garbage removal, sewage, pollution, income, taxes, budgets, happiness and tourism (and a few other things) to get the most out of your metropolis - but it's not as daunting as it sounds.I've heard this game described as a Sim City rip off.  I don't care if people think that it is. At worst, they took a deeply flawed product and did it right. At best, they've just produced a fine example of the city building genre.This game is a VERY good city builder. With a few tweaks from the devs, it could comfortably become the jewel in the crown of all city builder games... it's THAT good.   I'd hit he recommend button twice if it would let me."
