,Recommended,255710,17120360,"Posted: 19 July, 2015",all,Erathresh,"This game is currently the best city builder around.  If you have ever enjoyed a SimCity game, then I would highly recommend picking this up.  It's insanely moddable, and the maps are huge, especially if you mod out the default size limit.  Just a word of warning though -- if your computer is very old or underpowered, you may have trouble coping with a city with over 100,000 residents, especially if your game is heavily modded.  My computer just about hits the recommended settings, so it struggles a bit with my 130,000 population city if I run any other program at all in the background.As with any city builder, there isn't much to do once you unlock all of the buildings and do most of what you set out to do, but it's extremely addicting to keep growing your city and managing the inevitable problems that a massive city comes with.EDIT: I have a new rig and this game runs very, very smoothly now, 100+ FPS.  It's apparently very processor-intensive, so keep that in mind if you have a very old processor.  My old computer had a 2.93 GHz quad core i-7, and it could just about handle it.  If you have something beefier than that and a decent GPU, you should have no problem.  Anything less and you might run into trouble."
