76561197991344117,Recommended,255710,14981532,"Posted: 20 March, 2015",all,Victari,"Basically if you like city builder games, you need to play this one.pros-The menus are functional and streamlined with little or no fluff.-The mechanics are intuitive and simple, yet, difficult to master and balance.-Actual thought needs to go into planning out your city.-Game fully utilizes mods and the steam workshop (more games need to do this)-Nicely addictive gameplay. Prepare to lose a few days to this one.-Price point. At $30 this game is great value for money-City size. while the standard game will eventually let you purchase 9 2x2km squares, mods will let you buy up to 25.-This game run very well on my rig, and looks great too.Cons- I would have liked to see more buildings, only having a firehouse and a firestation for example feels lackluster. But mods can and do fix this issue.- AI can be a bit doofy sometimes. cars will stop in the middle of the road sometimes for no apparent reason causing traffic jams. Realistic I suppose but a little frustrating when one dummy clogs up a whole interchange. They also tend to drive all in single file lines a lot not using all of your nice 3 lane highways or strategically placed roundabouts.- The menus kinda look like cheap Iphone apps or something to me. they just dont have the polish that I was expecting. I am ok with this though, they are completely functional and it feels like the effort saved on not making the menus flashy was put into making the gameplay interesting.Other thoughts:This game can be very unforgiving. This may be a + or a - for you depending on how difficult you like it, but expect your city to die of plague or something first few times you play. My first city lost 40k population because everyone was over educated and wouldn't work in standard industry, and because my industry was dying, no goods were being produced and the economy crashed. I now know how to fix this, but it took some trial and error. I suppose I was lucky as it seems many other people's first cities died in toxic clouds of poo gas. 8.5/10 not perfect, but pretty dang good."
