,Recommended,255710,14846547,"Posted: 11 March, 2015",all,OPPDelta,"ImpressionsFrom the first 2 hours I can already comment the complexity of the simulation in this game is outstanding and runs really smooth, you don't get bogged down; The in game hints offer just what you need. Seems well optimised and has no game-breaking issues that I've stumbled upon yet. From a developer that created transport simulations before; This game holds nothing back. You WILL get traffic problems if you don't plan ahead and it's your job to fix it or problems arise in game. Things progressively get difficult as you expand into new building grids. The map size is huge for those who are worried. With a quick mod you can unlock the full map allowing you to build huge metropolis's. The game is so detailed you even rename pigs...After spending over 4 hours in the asset/mod manager alone just perfecting and learning the way roads form, with their one way systems or complex intersections and then to finally implement them and watch the traffic flow freely made me smile. Repeating on many reviews; This is the game SimCity should have been. With the built in map editor you can recreate your home town/city and see how the game stacks up against the real thing.With, already, hundreds of workshop items from the community ranging from; custom maps, buildings, highways, junctions and items you wont run out of ideas or playable maps any time soon. With fluid camera motions and a in-game ""Tilt Shift"" filter, there are some amazing screenshots around already.SummaryI really want to review more but I'd end up writing an essay. All in all I highly recommend this game for anyone, from casual to die hard city building fans. Both groups will find their niche."
