76561198046392587,Recommended,255710,21314809,"Posted: 19 February, 2016",all,jotaman82,"Cities: Skylines is, in lack of a better description, a super Sim City. Even in the game's community the inhabitants are referred to as ""cims"" (instead of ""sims"").When creating and growing cities, at first the challenge is about budgeting but soon the biggest challenge is about functionality - whether creating new neighbourhoods intelligently or micro-managing the ones that already exist. The ammount of micro-managing, especially traffic, is inversely proportional to the thought you put into creating new neighbourhoods.The game fools you into thinking ""hey, this is easy, i keep an eye on demands and create what they need and the city grows"" but then, when you notice, you have sick citizens because of pollution, burned down buildings because the fireman can't reach the fires, traffic jams that don't allow people to go to work or, even if they do, don't allow cargo trucks to keep the economy working, etc.One thing is for sure, after some hours playing this game, you will think about your own town's city planning whenever you go out and drive."
