76561198015087332,Recommended,255710,24905709,"Posted: 14 August, 2016",all,m85,I’ve always enjoyed SIM games and after not playing any for many years I decided to get back into SIM gaming. After a great deal of review I decided to purchase Cities: Skylines + After Dark add-on. Since I’ve played over 100 hours of this game within the past month I thought it would be appropriate to share my thoughts about this game. The vanilla game alone is outstanding. Once you have a good grasp of the game then add community made assets for an entirely new level of enjoyment and realism. The amount of detail and customization in this game is superb. From naming individuals living in your city to creating transit lines or even creating and adding your own home makes the level/asset editor great.The game does have hiccups here and there and it is disappointing when you like an asset and the creator removes it from STEAM for no reason but for the most part I am very happy with my purchase. Also loading times with added mods can be painfully long at times. However I would definitely recommend this game if you are looking to get into a city builder type of game.I would recommend studying real city layouts and reading some of the community written guides before attempting to build your city.
